The article is a statement by President Obama on the Senate's passage of the Family Smoking and Tobacco Control Act. The act has received bipartisan support and, once passed by the House, will give the FDA the power to take steps to reduce the harmful effects of tobacco and prevent its marketing to children. The President emphasizes the high healthcare costs and the number of young people becoming regular smokers. He states that his administration is committed to protecting children and reforming the healthcare system, and looks forward to signing the bill into law and working with the HHS Secretary and FDA Commissioner on its implementation.